To run the code on Linux:

- Set the SDK path in Makefile, 'make'.
- Run './soffice "--accept=socket,host=localhost,port=2083;urp;StarOffice.ServiceManager"':
  This starts LibreOffice in server mode.
- Run 'make run' to run the client code.

Same on Windows:

- Run cmd.exe, invoke 'setsdkenv_windows.bat' form the SDK, plain 'cppumaker' should output its usage if the SDK env is OK.
- Tweak the paths in Makefile as necessary, 'make'.
- Run 'soffice.exe "--accept=socket,host=localhost,port=2083;urp;StarOffice.ServiceManager"':
  This starts LibreOffice in server mode.
- Run 'test.exe -env:URE_MORE_TYPES="file:///c/progra~1/libreo~1/program/types/offapi.rdb" "file:///z:/libreoffice/lo-test-filters/test1.odt"'
  This runs the client code (Replace the z:/ URL with the URL of the current directory).
